data.title: Earl of Cornwall
data.text:
Earl of Cornwall Coat of arms of the 1st, and current Earl Blazon Quarterly, I & IV: Gules a hammer and sickle Or, II & III: Argent a saltire engrailed Azure, a chief Azure three cinquefoils Argent Creation date 2019 Created by John Peerage Peerage of Baustralia First holder Blair Hardwick, 1st Earl of Cornwall Present holder Blair Hardwick Remainder to the 1st Earls's heirs male of the body lawfully begotten.

Earl of Cornwall in the County of Cornwall in the province of Holderton, named after the former province of Cornwall, Baustralia, is a title that has been created once. The current holder is Blair Hardwick, 1st Earl of Cornwall.
